<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p></p><div class="quoteright" style="width:348px;"><div class="lazy_load_img_box" style="padding-top:91.95%"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/Yaiba_-_Copia_7372.jpg" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/Yaiba_-_Copia_7372.jpg" width="348" height="320"></div></div><div class="acaptionright" style="width:348px;">Yaiba holding the Raijin Katana, Sayaka and Onimaru</div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p><em>Yaiba</em> (<em>Ken'yu Densetsu Yaiba</em>/<em>Legend of the Swordsman Yaiba</em>) is a Shonen manga written by Gosho Aoyama, known for <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DetectiveConan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DetectiveConan">Detective Conan</a></em> and <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MagicKaito" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MagicKaito">Magic Kaito</a></em>. It starts out as a light, funny manga very similar to <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DragonBall" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DragonBall">Dragon Ball</a></em> but slowly becomes more serious towards the end.</p><p>The main character, Yaiba Kurogane is a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KidSamurai" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KidSamurai">Kid Samurai</a>, trained by his father Kenjuuro in a unspecified jungle. They both return to Japan where they're "hosted" by Raizo Mine, an old rival of Kenjuuro. Here Yaiba meets Sayaka, Raizo's daughter and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheRival" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheRival">Onimaru</a>, a highly skilled kendo master. To sum up, they become bitter rivals and Onimaru gets really obsessed with beating Yaiba. In order to do so, he tries to use the legendary <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoolSword" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoolSword">Fujin Katana</a> (Wind Devil Sword in some translations), which grants power over <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlowYouAway" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlowYouAway">Wind Gusts and Typhoons</a>, but the sword turns him into a evil Oni (demon) bent on conquering the World. In order to stop him, Yaiba, with the help of Sayaka and his pets Kagetora (<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CowardlyLion" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CowardlyLion">a cowardly Tiger</a>) and Shonosuke (a nice Vulture), goes on a quest to find and master the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShockAndAwe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShockAndAwe">Raijin Katana</a> (or Thunder God Sword), guarded by a 400 years old <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/MiyamotoMusashi" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/MiyamotoMusashi">Miyamoto Musashi</a>.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><p>An Anime was made, but it lasted only 52 episodes, covering the story from the beginning to Kaguya's Arc. Yaiba and friends appear in the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MassiveMultiplayerCrossover" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MassiveMultiplayerCrossover">Massive Multiplayer Crossover</a> game, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SundayVSMagazineShuuketsuChoujouDaikessen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SundayVSMagazineShuuketsuChoujouDaikessen">Sunday VS Magazine: Shuuketsu! Choujou Daikessen</a>.</p><p>Now it has a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Characters/Yaiba" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Characters/Yaiba">Characters Page</a>.</p><p></p><hr><h2><em>Yaiba</em> provides examples of:</h2><p></p><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AbsurdlySharpBlade" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AbsurdlySharpBlade">Absurdly Sharp Blade</a>: Many swords in series are really sharp. Justified, because they're <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AWizardDidIt" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AWizardDidIt">magical swords</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AchillesHeel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AchillesHeel">Achilles' Heel</a>: Many villains have these. Including Bat-Man (weak to sunlight), the Moon Bunnies (their ears) and Silver's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoForTheEye" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoForTheEye">eye</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccidentalPervert" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccidentalPervert">Accidental Pervert</a>: Jubei at least once. All others are plain perverts <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllMenArePerverts" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllMenArePerverts">and proud of it!</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Acrofatic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Acrofatic">Acrofatic</a>: Goemon Ishikawa is quite large and plump, but he's a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LightningBruiser" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LightningBruiser">Lightning Bruiser</a> when he fights.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationDistillation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationDistillation">Adaptation Distillation</a>: The anime. The most prominent example is the first episode which manages to cover the whole <em>first volume</em> in thirty minutes.</li><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AffablyEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AffablyEvil">Affably Evil</a>: Goemon, who after all, enjoys drinking sake and wouldn't hurt animals no matter what. Also Kaguya, who flirted with Onimaru... before <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WorfEffect" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WorfEffect">parrying his wind slash with her fan</a> an tossing a huge ki blast at him.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AirJousting" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AirJousting">Air Jousting</a>: Whenever Yaiba have to face a flying opponent. Usually with a little help from Shonosuke and later with the Ryujin Katana.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllYourPowersCombined" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllYourPowersCombined">All Your Powers Combined</a>: The Ryujin (Dragon-God) Orb can use the powers of the other seven Legendary Orbs and some other tricks. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> during the last battle against Kaguya, he must use this very trope in order to awaken the true power of the Dragon God</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlluringAnglerfish" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlluringAnglerfish">Alluring Anglerfish</a>: Yakitori, one of Onimaru's Shitenno in the Onimaru's Fortress arc. It actually has a Japanese paper lantern attached to it, and he's very proud of it. Oh, and don't call him <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton">"Toadstool"</a>....</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AncestralWeapon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AncestralWeapon">Ancestral Weapon</a>: Both Raijin and Fujin Swords are really old weapons from the past. Also many other swords.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnguishedDeclarationOfLove" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnguishedDeclarationOfLove">Anguished Declaration of Love</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Yaiba says a "I Like You, seriously." to an aged Sayaka before confronting Kaguya. After the battle however he jokes about it, so we don't know if it was serious or not</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimeHair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimeHair">Anime Hair</a>: Yaiba. Also Kotaro and Goemon, whose hair resembles an afro.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArtificialHuman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArtificialHuman">Artificial Human</a>:<ul><li> The last guardians of the Pyramid, namely Ruby, Sapphire, Diamond <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> and Emerald</span>.</li><li> Gozuma from the Platina Corporation is a partial exception: He's fully human, but underwent a special operation in order to have some chips planted in his muscles, making him the perfect warrior.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArrogantKungFuGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArrogantKungFuGuy">Arrogant Kung-Fu Guy</a>: Takeshi Onimaru, before and after his transformation. Also Gekkou the Black Moon Bunny and Budou the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItMakesSenseInContext" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItMakesSenseInContext">Grape Soldier</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AttackAttackAttack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AttackAttackAttack">Attack! Attack! Attack!</a>: Yaiba's trademark strategy. Of course, if this doesn't work he's more than capable of finding out a solution against his foes.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AttackItsWeakPoint" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AttackItsWeakPoint">Attack Its Weak Point</a>:<ul><li> Done during the battle against Gold and Silver in the Underworld arc. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> it doesn't really work as well as hoped</span>.</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Yaiba defeat both Orochi and Onimaru by cutting their horns</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AttackOfThe50FootWhatever" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AttackOfThe50FootWhatever">Attack of the 50-Foot Whatever</a>: This is the power of the Giant Orb of the Great Buddha of Nara. Also is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CastFromHitPoints" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CastFromHitPoints">Cast From Hit Points</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAvatar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAvatar">Author Avatar</a>:<ul><li> Gosho's name (or Gosho himself) tends to pop up frequently here and there.</li><li> He also appears along with the other characters (who refuse to acknowledge him and mercilessly mock him) in the Omake. He takes part in the race with the others but get <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoltOfDivineRetribution" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoltOfDivineRetribution">zapped by God</a> for cheating.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnAxeToGrind" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnAxeToGrind">An Axe to Grind</a>: Gerozaemon's weapon of choice. Also the Rock Soldier and Ruby in the Pyramid Arc.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadAssBeard" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadAssBeard">Bad Ass Beard</a>: Young Musashi sports one. He shaved himself before facing Kojiro at Ganryujima.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadAssCreed" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadAssCreed">Bad Ass Creed</a>: The magical writings on the Fujin sword, that explain how to master it. Sadly, it' quickly forgotten.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadAssMoustache" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadAssMoustache">Bad Ass Moustache</a>: Ryujin.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadPowersBadPeople" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadPowersBadPeople">Bad Powers, Bad People</a>: The Devil King Sword. In this case, the more wicked the wielder is, the more powerful it becomes.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BaldOfEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BaldOfEvil">Bald of Evil</a>: Onimaru Takeshi sports one. Also the fallen monk <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBrute" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBrute">Seikai Miyoshi</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BarrierWarrior" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BarrierWarrior">Barrier Warrior</a>: One of the powers of Ryujin's sword allows Yaiba to create an energy shield. Emerald is capable of summoning Barriers and healing people. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Actually, she Is the Barrier Soldier</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BatOutOfHell" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BatOutOfHell">Bat Out of Hell</a>: The strongest of the Hakki, the Batman (or Bat-Guy in the anime). See also <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OurVampiresAreDifferent" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OurVampiresAreDifferent">Our Vampires Are Different</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleAmongstTheFlames" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleAmongstTheFlames">Battle Amongst the Flames</a>:The final battle during the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/OdaNobunaga" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/OdaNobunaga">Oda Nobunaga</a> Tournament takes place in a copy of the Temple of Honnoji (where Nobunaga met his doom) and, just to fit the atmosphere, the shrine is set ablaze with fire arrows!</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleAura" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleAura">Battle Aura</a>: Many fighters. Also shown as a power with <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> the Toujin (Battle Blades), a flurry of "ghost slices" that attacks the enemy from many directions and can only be "felt".</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BearsAreBadNews" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BearsAreBadNews">Bears Are Bad News</a>: Goemon Ishikawa can transform into a huge bear wearing a really hard armor.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BeethovenWasAnAlienSpy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BeethovenWasAnAlienSpy">Beethoven Was an Alien Spy</a>: The famous poet Matsuo Basho was actually a vicious assassin who wanted to use Ryujin's powers to take over the world, but died of illness while on his quest. And now Onimaru has resurrected him...</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BFG" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BFG">BFG</a>: The Carbon-Freeze cannon and Gekko's Moonclub, which doubles as a Bazooka.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BFS" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BFS">BFS</a>:<ul><li> Despite having a lot of swords and weapons, Aoyama rarely uses this trope. Yet, Kojiro's Laundry Pole has the power to grow really really long.</li><li> Also the Devil King Sword (Mao Ken) is quite large compared to Gekko. Gold in the Underworld arc wields a gargantuan scimitar, but is quite justified because it fit its size.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBad">Big Bad</a>:<ul><li> Onimaru Takeshi, your typical overlord. Also Kaguya and, during the Pyramid and Underworld arcs, Boss.</li><li> In the last arc the Platina Company.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBadWannabe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBadWannabe">Big Bad Wannabe</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStarscream" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStarscream">Basho Matsuo</a> want to find the Ryujin Orb and use its power to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakeOverTheWorld" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakeOverTheWorld">Take Over the World</a>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigEater" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigEater">Big Eater</a>:<ul><li> Yaiba, Gerozaemon and Musashi, expecially Musashi, during the firsts arc. Musashi in his first appearence was able to steal and devour a whole roasted boar in about two panels or so.</li><li> This was used by the Spiderman to tend a trap to them twice. And <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RuleOfFunny" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RuleOfFunny">they fell for it twice!</a>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigGood" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigGood">Big Good</a>: Ryujin the Dragon-God. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Also Susanoo during the Yamata no Orochi arc</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigDamnHeroes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigDamnHeroes">Big Damn Heroes</a>: Happens from time to time. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> During Orochi arc, Ryujin does this in order to save Yaiba and Sayaka from Dark</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigOlEyebrows" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigOlEyebrows">Big Ol' Eyebrows</a>: Musashi sports overly long eyebrows, long enough to make any <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/WorldOfWarcraft" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/WorldOfWarcraft">Blood Elf</a> jealous.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BizarroUniverse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BizarroUniverse">Bizarro Universe</a>:<ul><li> There's a small world inside the Darkness Orb: it looks like a black swamp with the kanji for "Darkness" in the sky, a watermill and a small mountain with a waterfall. Also, the ground is composed by the remains of the previous victims who<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndIMustScream" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndIMustScream">died of old age without finding a way out</a>. The only way out is hidden behind the waterfall, but is guarded by a giant fire-breathing carnivorous Kappa named <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FluffyTheTerrible" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FluffyTheTerrible">Kerosuke</a>.</li><li> On the other hand, all your wishes (except leaving the Orb) can become true.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BladeBelowTheShoulder" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BladeBelowTheShoulder">Blade Below the Shoulder</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Unlike the other Demons, Plasma uses two triangular blades protunding from his forearms.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BladeOnAStick" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BladeOnAStick">Blade on a Stick</a>: The Snakeman wields the Snake-God Pike (a four pronged elaborated spear), who is said to be unbreakable. Also <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilSorcerer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilSorcerer">Shiro Amakusa</a> can make a golden spear out of his hair.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlandNameProduct" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlandNameProduct">Bland-Name Product</a>: ONY televisions.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BloodlessCarnage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BloodlessCarnage">Bloodless Carnage</a>: Semi-averted: Yaiba often bleeds when he gets hurt, but not too much.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlowYouAway" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlowYouAway">Blow You Away</a>: The powers of the Fujin Orb, and Onimaru's specialty. Later, Yaiba too when he obtain the Fujin Sword.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoobsOfSteel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoobsOfSteel">Boobs of Steel</a>: Kaguya is the most powerful female character in Yaiba, and sports the largest bosom. Granted, not that there <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSmurfettePrinciple" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSmurfettePrinciple">are many others female characters</a>, mind you. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Subverted by her true form for obvious reasons</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoobyTrap" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoobyTrap">Booby Trap</a>: Whenever they have to face a Dungeon/Fortress, there will be traps. Also Goemon uses them in the Showdown vs Yaiba at Kawanakajima.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoozeBasedBuff" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoozeBasedBuff">Booze-Based Buff</a>: When Jubei get drunk, his dark side awakes and he transform himself into a wicked, drunk wolf.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrainwashedAndCrazy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrainwashedAndCrazy">Brainwashed and Crazy</a>:<ul><li> Onimaru did this to the Japanese Ministers in order to take over Japan.</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> After being defeated by Yaiba, is revealed that Onimaru was always like this since he mastered the Fujin Katana and grew horns, and has no memory of what he have done before</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreakableWeapons" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreakableWeapons">Breakable Weapons</a>: Happens often with Musashi's and Jubei's katana, and with Laundry Pole (in that case the blade can grow back). Also the so-called Invincible Snake-God Pike and even Fujin Sword ( It got better). <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> During the Yamata no Orochi arc, Yaiba's Supreme King Sword started cracking after blocking Onimaru's strongest attack only to grow even stronger later when the blade shattered and reveald its full power. The same goes for the Devil King Sword</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreathWeapon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreathWeapon">Breath Weapon</a>: Kotaro's Fire Ring Justu. Also <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Demon-Gold</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButtMonkey" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButtMonkey">Butt-Monkey</a>: Oooh boy, poor little Spiderman is a huge one. Onimaru never misses a chance for punishing him, insulting him and hanging him out of the fortress with a rope. He drop this habit later.<div class="indent"> <strong>Spiderman</strong>: "Onimaru-samaaaaaaa!!! Please Forgive meeeeeeee!!!"</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallingYourAttacks" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallingYourAttacks">Calling Your Attacks</a>:<ul><li> Yaiba Yaiba Yaiba. Also Onimaru and some of his enemies are guilty of this sometimes, often with bits of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GratuitousEnglish" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GratuitousEnglish">Gratuitous English</a>.</li><li> Let's not forget Kojiro, whose Sword need a special command ("Grow Laundy Pole!") in order to activate his powers. Is really noticeable in the Spanish dub of the Anime..</li></ul><div class="indent"> <strong>Kojiro</strong>:"<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoIndoorVoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoIndoorVoice">ADELANTE ESPADA MAGICA! ENLARGATE!!!</a>"</div><ul><li> In the last arc, Juubei was guilty of this.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Came