i.php/Manga/DragonBall">Kami</a>.</li><li> According to <img src="/images/article-hreficon-trivia.png" class="trivia1 rounded" title="This example contains a TRIVIA entry. It should be moved to the TRIVIA tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod">Aoyama</a>, Yaiba himself is modeled after Teppei Uesugi from <em>Ore wa Teppei</em></li></ul></li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EyeScream" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EyeScream">Eye Scream</a>: How Silver is taken out. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> That's not enough to kill him</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FaceHeelTurn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FaceHeelTurn">Face&#150;Heel Turn</a>: The Mushroom Soldier can do this if you eat one of his mushrooms, which grows in abundance in his chamber.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Filler" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Filler">Filler</a>: A whole volume worth of it!</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FiveManBand" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FiveManBand">Five-Man Band</a>: Both Kaguya, Boss and Onimaru (latest arc)<ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBad">Big Bad</a>: Kaguya / Boss / Onimaru</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDragon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDragon">The Dragon</a>: Gekko / Jewel or Gold&amp;Silver / Dark</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheEvilGenius" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheEvilGenius">The Evil Genius</a>: Tsukikage / Diamond / <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Plasma</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBrute" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBrute">The Brute</a>: Mangetsu / Ruby / Burner</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDarkChick" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDarkChick">The Dark Chick</a>: Hangetsu / Sapphire / Rain.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlamingSword" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlamingSword">Flaming Sword</a>: Yaiba when using the Fire Orb. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> or the Supreme King Sword for the first time</span>. Also Gold who can heat up his blade. And let's not forget Burner's Fire Demon Longsword, who can set fire to everything it touches. Kojiro learnt that in the worst way possible.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FourIsDeath" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FourIsDeath">Four Is Death</a>: Onimaru's Shitenno, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> and later his Four Demons</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FreezeRay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FreezeRay">Freeze Ray</a>: The Carbon Freeze Cannon.</li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FusionDance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FusionDance">Fusion Dance</a>: Moonfolk's Getai power. Diamond and the other Soldiers uses this to create the allmighty Jewel.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FuumaShuriken" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FuumaShuriken">Fuuma Shuriken</a>: Oddly, it's not used by the epynimous Kotaro, but by Goemon Ishikawa in his Bear form.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GagPenis" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GagPenis">Gag Penis</a>: It's implied that Yaiba got one when he used the power of the Giant Orb for the first time.<div class="indent"> <strong>Yaiba</strong>: "Ooooohh!!! That one too got Huge!!!"</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiantEnemyCrab" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiantEnemyCrab">Giant Enemy Crab</a>: Mangetsu demonstrate the power of "Getai" (<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FusionDance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FusionDance">merging</a>) on a lobster.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiantSpider" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiantSpider">Giant Spider</a>: The Spiderman, who is probably the cutest, funniest <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiantSpider" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiantSpider">Giant Spider</a> ever!</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiveMeASword" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiveMeASword">Give Me a Sword</a>: When <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Kaguya swallows the Sword of Raijin, Onimaru gives Yaiba the Fujin Sword so he can use the Ryujin Orb with it. Also because he intended to acquire the far more powerful Devil King Sword</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GodIsEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GodIsEvil">God Is Evil</a>:<ul><li> Amakusa tries to summon up to 36 gods to find out the location of the Legendary Orb of Kyushu, but he's hilariously unsuccessful. Also "God" in the Chiki Chiki Grand Prix Omake is shown as fat and lazy, and want to start a Galactic War just to win the boredom. He also really likes sports.</li><li> Averted with Ryujin <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> and Susanoo</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GracefulLoser" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GracefulLoser">Graceful Loser</a>: Jubei, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Soshi Okita and, basically, all the millionairs who bet in the Oda Nobunaga Tournament to Yaiba.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GratuitousEnglish" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GratuitousEnglish">Gratuitous English</a>: Many techniques. The Batman in the Japanese/Italian/Spanish/Non-English-speaking countries is a huge offender.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GratuitousFrench" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GratuitousFrench">Gratuitous French</a>: Chamaleon Bonaparte, "<em>Le Roi Malefique</em>" of Lord Onimaru.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Hammerspace" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Hammerspace">Hammerspace</a>: Many people are guilty of this, including Kotaro Fuuma, Goemon Ishikawa and Benkei, whose weapons seem to materialize out of thin air. Averted somehow with Silver, who keep his huge Ball&amp;Chain inside his stomach.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HandsomeLech" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HandsomeLech">Handsome Lech</a>: Kojiro Sasaki. He's a living "Pretty Girls Radar".</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeelFaceRevolvingDoor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeelFaceRevolvingDoor">Heel&#150;Face Revolving Door</a>: A running gag with Kojiro during the Onimaru Fortress arc. This backfires hilariously when he seriously try to backstab his fellows.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeelFaceTurn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeelFaceTurn">Heel&#150;Face Turn</a>: Gerozaemon, the Seacucumberman, Kojiro, Jubei. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Kaguya after the Orochi Arc, who decides to give up conquering earth and return on the moon</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicSacrifice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicSacrifice">Heroic Sacrifice</a>:<ul><li> Jubei is quite prone to these, also <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> almost everyone in the Ryujin's trials, but they <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnexplainedRecovery" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnexplainedRecovery">got better</a>. Emerald did this and she <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KilledOffForReal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KilledOffForReal">didn't</a> .</span></li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> When Ryujin got caught in Dark's Super Delta Zone attack, he puts a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakingYouWithMe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakingYouWithMe">Taking You with Me</a> in order to drag that evil monster with him.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicBSOD" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicBSOD">Heroic BSoD</a>: Yaiba has had only two short ones: first when Onimaru kicked his ass with the Fujin sword and later when <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> he's utterly bested by Gekko and Sayaka choose to follow him in order to save Yaiba's life</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HistoricalDomainCharacter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HistoricalDomainCharacter">Historical Domain Character</a>: Many, including, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/MiyamotoMusashi" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/MiyamotoMusashi">Miyamoto Musashi</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/SasakiKojiro" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/SasakiKojiro">Sasaki Kojiro</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/FuumaKotaro" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/FuumaKotaro">Fuuma Kotaro</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/YagyuJubei" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/YagyuJubei">Yagyu Jubei</a>. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/HattoriHanzo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/HattoriHanzo">Hattori Hanzo</a> gets a cameo during the Oda Nobunaga Tournament.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HoistByHisOwnPetard" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HoistByHisOwnPetard">Hoist by His Own Petard</a>:<ul><li> Kojiro is defeated by Jubei when he proves the lenght of his sword by standing on it and stretching it to the clouds. Jubei' answer? Kicking the blade and making him fall from Niigata to Tokyo. At least he landed in the women Dojo...</li><li> More seriously with Goemon and his Shurikens.</li><li> Silver got electrocuted by his own laser beam.</li><li> Dark <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> fall victim of his own Super Delta Zone attack, courtesy of Ryujin. see above</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HollywoodChameleons" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HollywoodChameleons">Hollywood Chameleons</a>: Chameleon Bonaparte again, who can basically turn invisible and even shapeshift into another person.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IWasQuiteALooker" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IWasQuiteALooker">I Was Quite a Looker</a>: Musashi. And he still think he's at least decent.<div class="indent"> <strong>Kojiro</strong>:" And what happended to your face, (althought it wasn't as pretty as mine) Uh!?"</div><div class="indent"> <strong>Musashi</strong> (calmly):" Hey, I'm still attractive!"</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IaijutsuPractitioner" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IaijutsuPractitioner">Iaijutsu Practitioner</a>: The Yokoichimonji attack. Performed by <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Devil King Onimaru</span> and Yaiba.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheIdiotFromOsaka" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheIdiotFromOsaka">The Idiot from Osaka</a>: Spiderman is a parody of Osaka people, expecially at first. He also speaks with Kansai dialect.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IdiotHero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.