oduced Yaiba's sister and mother.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadScientist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadScientist">Mad Scientist</a>: Professor Kanabo, who works for Onimaru. He double as a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CloudCuckooLander" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CloudCuckooLander">Cloud Cuckoo Lander</a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadeOfIron" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadeOfIron">Made of Iron</a>: Almost everyone. Except poor Musashi of course..</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MakingASplash" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MakingASplash">Making a Splash</a>: The Water Orb of Suijin allows Yaiba to manipulate masses of water. Rain is the Water Demon. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Later Sayaka masters the Water Demon Longsword, but she can't use its full power.</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheManBehindTheMan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheManBehindTheMan">The Man Behind the Man</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Come on Boss, I know you hate humans, but how could you trust Onimaru!?? <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatAnIdiot" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatAnIdiot">What an Idiot!</a>!</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasterOfIllusion" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasterOfIllusion">Master of Illusion</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Plasma can use light to create perfect illusions and mirages of the surrounding enviroment</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasterSwordsman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasterSwordsman">Master Swordsman</a>: Several, including Musashi, Kojiro, Jubei, Yaiba, Onimaru and Soshi Okita. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Kenjuuro too.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MarshmallowHell" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MarshmallowHell">Marshmallow Hell</a>:<ul><li> During the Yaiba/Shiro transformation duel the latter turned himself into a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlayboyBunny" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlayboyBunny">Playboy Bunny</a> girl. After a beat, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AttractiveBentGender" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AttractiveBentGender">Yaiba went to her and get this one</a>.</li><li> Also when he's being healed by Emerald, he starts nosebleeding when he realize that she's holding him against her breasts. Sayaka wasn't amused..</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MeaningfulName" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MeaningfulName">Meaningful Name</a>:<ul><li> Many: Yaiba Kurogane means "Black Steel Blade". Kenjuuro (his father) means "Ten Swords". Onimaru means, of course, Oni (Ogre or Demon).</li><li> The Moonfolk are named after moon phases and terms (Tsukikage and Gekko, for example, mean Moonbeams and Moonlight).</li><li> Onimaru's demons have these: Rain, Burner, Dark <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> and Plasma</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MiniatureSeniorCitizens" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MiniatureSeniorCitizens">Miniature Senior Citizens</a>: Musashi and Sayaka's Grandmother.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MisplacedWildlife" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MisplacedWildlife">Misplaced Wildlife</a>: .... Gorillas... in Japan?</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MissingMom" title="/p