zed Powerhouse</a>: Yaiba. Small but awfully powerful!</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrecisionFStrike" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrecisionFStrike">Precision F-Strike</a>: Batman said "God Damn" as he's sliced in half by Yaiba's Senpuken (whirlwind sword).</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrehensileHair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrehensileHair">Prehensile Hair</a>: Kaguya's trump card agaisnt Onimaru, and it worked.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrettyInMink" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrettyInMink">Pretty in Mink</a>: Princess Kaguya's bunny suit, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PimpedOutCape" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PimpedOutCape">cape</a>, and gloves are trimmed with white fur.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PunnyName" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PunnyName">Punny Name</a>: Many of them. Often with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BilingualBonus" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BilingualBonus">Bilingual Bonus</a><ul><li> The main one is Professor Kanabo ("Mano de Hierro" in the Spanish dub), whose name literally means "Iron Club". Kanabo's were said to be Oni's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice">Weapon of Choice</a> and there are many japanese proverbs about Oni's with Iron Clubs being stronger or even invincible. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging">Lampshade Hanging</a> by Spiderman.</li></ul><div class="indent"> <strong>Spiderman</strong>:" As they say, a Oni with a Kanabo becomes even stronger!!"</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/QuirkyMinibossSquad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/QuirkyMinibossSquad">Quirky Miniboss Squad</a>: The Hyakki, then the Shitenno, the Moon Generals, the Soldiers and Onimaru's Demons.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Raiju" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Raiju">Raiju</a>: Shiro Amakusa turns into a giant, six tailed weasel with huge claws for his showdown with the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KidSamurai" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KidSamurai">Kid Samurai</a>. However, he doesn't gain any thunder-related ability.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RazorWind" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RazorWind">Razor Wind</a>:<ul><li> Onimaru's main form of attack, both with Wind and Thunder. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> later with the Maoken's Crescent Moon Blast</span>.</li><li> Also Kotaro's Fuuma Ninpo Kamaitachi, which uses the vacuum to create slicing wind gusts. Or something like that.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedBaron" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedBaron">Red Baron</a>: Onimaru eventually call himself "Devil King Onimaru". Also Frederick Luther's, a.k.a the "Black Baron". (<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MadWorld" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MadWorld">Stop staring!</a>)</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedOniBlueOni" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedOniBlueOni">Red Oni, Blue Oni</a>: Or rather Raijin and Fujin. In any case, Yaiba and Onimaru.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ResetButton" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ResetButton">Reset Button</a>: After Kaguya's and <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Orochi</span>'s arc everything is back to normal, despite all.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RivalTurnedEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RivalTurnedEvil">Rival Turned Evil</a>: Takeshi Onimaru.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RubberMan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RubberMan">Rubber Man</a>: Silver and Gold have super-bouncy (No, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JigglePhysics" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JigglePhysics">not ''that'' kind of bouncy</a>) hides that can repeal even the mightiest swordstrikes. They can also strecth their arms. Yet, they seems to be sensitive to heat. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Silver got sliced in half by Gold's superheated sabre and Gold was pierced by Yaiba's super powered Supreme King sword.</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RuleOfCool" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RuleOfCool">Rule of Cool</a>: Seriously, some of the stuff that happens in this manga can be really over-the-top sometimes...</li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScaryImpracticalArmor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScaryImpracticalArmor">Scary Impractical Armor</a>: Onimaru sports one, which is not impractical and has a long cloak and Jetpack.<ul><li> It is only impractical against heat as the Chiki Chiki Grand Prix Omake shown:</li></ul><div class="indent"> (while crossing desert)<strong>Onimaru</strong>:" Ufff...ufff... is really... hot there..."</div><div class="indent"> <strong>Spiderman</strong>:" If it's so hot... <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging">why don't you just take off that heavy armor?</a></div><div class="indent"> <strong>Onimaru</strong>:" You FOOL! I can't just take off MY armor, The SYMBOL Of EVIL!!!"</div><ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Hilariously, when Onimaru is fred by the demonic possession, he claims that his armor looks ridicolous</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SealedEvilInACan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SealedEvilInACan">Sealed Evil in a Can</a>:<ul><li> Onimaru is frozen by Kaguya's Carbon Freeze Cannon. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> also Kaguya and Orochi later</span>.</li><li> Also Gekko, who was imprisoned for trying to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStarscream" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStarscream">take over the moon</a> in the past and was released to fight Yaiba.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SealedInsideAPersonShapedCan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SealedInsideAPersonShapedCan">Sealed Inside a Person-Shaped Can</a>: Kaguya is locked into the Dragon Prietess's body.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SecretTestOfCharacter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SecretTestOfCharacter">Secret Test of Character</a>: Yaiba is forced to choose between the last of the Legendary Orbs and saving all of his friends that have been falling in each of the trials. Yaiba chooses the latter, and he earns the Legendary Orb because of this.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SelfDuplication" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SelfDuplication">Self-Duplication</a>: Burner can make four clones of himself made out of flames.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SensibleHeroesSkimpyVillains" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SensibleHeroesSkimpyVillains">Sensible Heroes, Skimpy Villains</a>: Princess Kaguya's outfit compared to the heroes' outfits.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShockAndAwe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShockAndAwe">Shock and Awe</a>: The Raijin Orb. Only Yaiba, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChosenOne" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChosenOne">The Chosen One</a> can use it safely... oh, Onimaru as well..</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShouldersOfDoom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShouldersOfDoom">Shoulders of Doom</a>: Everyone with a cloak.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut">Shout-Out</a>: Seen <a class="urllink" href="https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ShoutOut/Yaiba">here<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SimultaneousBladeSpam" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SimultaneousBladeSpam">Simultaneous Blade Spam</a>: The Toujin (Battle Blade) attack can do this, but with etheral blades which distract the opponent.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SinisterScythe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SinisterScythe">Sinister Scythe</a>: Basho has a cool scythe. Also Diamond's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice">Weapon of Choice</a>. Doubles as a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnergyWeapon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnergyWeapon">Energy Weapon</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SlasherSmile" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SlasherSmile">Slasher Smile</a>: Silver and Gold do this a lot.</li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StockNinjaWeaponry" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StockNinjaWeaponry">Stock Ninja Weaponry</a>: Kotaro uses a lot of ninja weapons, including a Shinobigatana, kunai, shuriken and even a Kusarigama. Later, Ishikawa Goemon is shown using kunai, smoke bombs and sai.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperIntelligence" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperIntelligence">Super Intelligence</a>: Diamond, the Genius Soldier to the point of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CombatClairvoyance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CombatClairvoyance">Combat Clairvoyance</a>. Also Sapphire the Skilled Soldier, which can replicate <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MirrorBoss" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MirrorBoss">each and every technique as she sees it in action</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperMode" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperMode">Super Mode</a>: Yaiba has done this various times.</li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakenForGranite" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakenForGranite">Taken for Granite</a>:<ul><li> Basho uses magical needles that turn people to stone. Apparently, making staues was a Hobby of his...</li><li> Also Onimaru after getting blasted by the Carbon Freeze Cannon.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakingTheBullet" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakingTheBullet">Taking the Bullet</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Onimaru to Yaiba of all People!!! Also Emerald.</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakingYouWithMe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakingYouWithMe">Taking You with Me</a>: All the Pyramid Soldiers explode after being killed. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Later Ryuujin trapped in the Super Delta Zone charges Dark and absorbs him too inside the barrier, which send them both in another dimension</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Tanuki" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Tanuki">Tanuki</a>: The guardians of the Golden Orb, who later help Yaiba against Kotaro. They also have <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GagPenis" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GagPenis">Gag Testicles</a>. The spell of the Tanuki is "pon poko pon poko pon poko pon poko ....."</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TeamPet" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TeamPet">Team Pet</a>: the Seacucumberman. yes, he actually exists. And is as lame as it sounds.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThatsNoMoon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThatsNoMoon">That's No Moon!</a>: When Yaiba and Onimaru <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> see that Kaguya's true head on her "body".</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThemeTuneCameo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThemeTuneCameo">Theme Tune Cameo</a>: Yaiba and the gang sing the end theme while in disguise from Kojiro.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThreateningShark" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThreateningShark">Threatening Shark</a>: Moon General Mikazuki "merge" with a shark in order to fight Yaiba underwater.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TigerVersusDragon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TigerVersusDragon">Tiger Versus Dragon</a>: During the battle vs Amakusa, Yaiba turns into a little humanoid dragon and Shiro into a huge white tiger.<div class="indent"> <strong>Musashi</strong>:" <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging">This is indeed the battle of a Tiger against a Dragon..</a>"</div><div class="indent"> <strong>Kojiro</strong>:" I don't think so...".</div></li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TookALevelInBadAss" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TookALevelInBadAss">Took A Level In Bad Ass</a>: Yaiba over time. Onimaru after turning into a Oni. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Sayaka mastering the Water Demon Longsword and containing Kaguya inside her body.</span>.</li></ul><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnholyNuke" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnholyNuke">Unholy Nuke</a>: The Devil King Sword's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EarthShatteringKaboom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EarthShatteringKaboom">Full Moon Blast</a>, used by Onimaru. Furthermore, all the attacks performed with the Devil King Sword are fueled by the negative feelings of the wielder.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VerbalTic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VerbalTic">Verbal Tic</a>: Some of Onimaru's minions.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainWithGoodPublicity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainWithGoodPublicity">Villain with Good Publicity</a>: The people of Japan don't seem to upset at the idea of having a fiendsih sword-wielding Oni as leader. Granted, he had brainwashed the ministries into submission, but still.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VoluntaryShapeshifting" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VoluntaryShapeshifting">Voluntary Shapeshifting</a>: The Gold Orb of the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Tanuki" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Tanuki">Tanuki</a> Kincho. Also Amakusa, and the Moon Bunnies.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WaveMotionGun" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WaveMotionGun">Wave-Motion Gun</a>:<ul><li> The Onimaru Cannon. it can shoot rays from Mount Fuji to Osaka!</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> also Kaguya's and Orochi's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreathWeapon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreathWeapon">Breath Weapon</a></span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WaxOnWaxOff" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WaxOnWaxOff">Wax On, Wax Off</a>: Musashi's main method of training include: building a whole wooden hut, doing houseworks, running away from restaurants after eating without paying the bill and going around selling newspapers. The last one while wearing <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven">''huge iron getas''</a> which leaves deep tracks in concrete...</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaksauceWeakness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaksauceWeakness">Weaksauce Weakness</a>:<ul><li> All the Hakki has at least one: Gerozaemon is scared by snakes, the Snakeman needs his tail to stay balanced. Slugman is shrink by salt, Spiderman is stunned by strong noises, Batman is scorched by sunlight, the Starfishman is withered by fire and the Seacucumberman is.. well.. is just weak.</li><li> Kojiro's sword will instantly grow several yards long if wet by salt water.</li><li> Also Kaguya, who will eventually turn into a old hag and die if she doesn't feed on a young girl.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WellIntentionedExtremist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WellIntentionedExtremist">Well-Intentioned Extremist</a>: Boss <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> mainly becaues <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumansAreTheRealMonsters" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumansAreTheRealMonsters">Humans Are the Real Monsters</a> and he want to stop their pollution of Planet Earth.</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatHappenedToTheMouse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatHappenedToTheMouse">What Happened to the Mouse?</a>: The whereabouts of many secondary characters is unknown. Including Onimaru's Grandfather and sister in the manga, the Mantisman, Hangestu-(in the anime, it's shown he was <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IncrediblyLamePun" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IncrediblyLamePun">fired</a> by Gekko.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhenTreesAttack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhenTreesAttack">When Trees Attack</a>: The Sugen Pollen Soldier. (Sugen is a sort of Japanese Mapple tree]].</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhereAreTheyNowEpilogue" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhereAreTheyNowEpilogue">"Where Are They Now?" Epilogue</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">The final chapter with a last twist of open ending.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WickedWeasel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WickedWeasel">Wicked Weasel</a>: Expecially if we're talking of a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Youkai" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Youkai">Giant Six-Tailed Weasel (Raiju)</a> with huge claws.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WoobieDestroyerOfWorlds" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WoobieDestroyerOfWorlds">Woobie, Destroyer of Worlds</a>: Gekko in the Anime, who was mistreated when he was a child because he was the only black moon rabbit.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WoodenKatanasAreEvenBetter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WoodenKatanasAreEvenBetter">Wooden Katanas Are Even Better</a>: When arriving at Yoroi Island for the Oda Nobunaga Tournament, Yaiba has the chance of choose a weapon among very famous swords, including the Muramasa and Samonji swords. He keeps his father's Bokken. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Onimaru, who was trained by Kenjuro himself, uses a Bokken too, and can use it to crush whole areas of ground with one blow.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WorfEffect" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WorfEffect">Worf Effect</a>: Many of Yaiba's techniques, including the Kaminarigiri.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YamatoNadeshiko" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YamatoNadeshiko">Yamato Nadeshiko</a>: Parodied by the beautiful <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LadyOfWar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LadyOfWar">Lady of War</a> Nadeshiko Yamato, a Naginata-wielding girl who wants to marry Yaiba at all costs.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouHaveFailedMe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouHaveFailedMe">You Have Failed Me</a>: Kaguya blasted Mangestu to oblivion after he failed his plan to kill Yaiba.</li></ul><p></p><hr>
